    "tool": "create_issue",
    "input": {
      "assignees": [],
      "body": "## Problem\nHarmonyEncoding tokenizer loading can run into threading issues when multiple threads request tokenizer file downloads at the same time. Concurrent access during initialization may allow overlapping downloads or reads before a tokenizer asset is fully available.\n\nThis affects the race condition discussed in #6 and also interacts with the offline loading requirement from #1.\n\n## Root Cause\nThe current loading path does not provide file locking around tokenizer file downloads. Without mutex-based file locking, multiple threads can attempt to create, update, or read tokenizer files concurrently, causing inconsistent state or partially written files.\n\n## Expected Solution\n- Add a shared mutex guard around tokenizer file downloads to serialize concurrent access.\n- Ensure HarmonyEncoding initialization is safe when multiple threads request the same encoding.\n- Provide a clear offline loading API path for local tokenizer files as requested in #1.\n- Document the race condition mitigation and link it back to #6.\n- Use mutex-based file locking to prevent overlapping download/write operations.",
