    "input": {
      "body": "Technical analysis: using `OnceLock` to lazily initialize a shared `mutex` is a reasonable thread safety mechanism for protecting tokenizer loading from concurrent access. The guard ensures only one caller can enter the download/loading critical section at a time, preventing overlapping tokenizer file downloads and avoiding race conditions caused by partially written files. This also complements issue #1 by keeping the offline loading capability separate through the file-based API, so local loading can avoid network download contention while still sharing the same HarmonyEncoding surface.",
